      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like you're treating both sides as equally valid when one side is basically just using linguistic gymnastics to ignore the literal text. isn't it more accurate to say that the originalist view is the only one grounded in actual history, while the other side is just a modern reinterpretation designed to serve an activist agenda?",
