      "content": "The originalist view is certainly rooted in historical texts and the perceived intent of the time. However, the \"living constitutionalist\" approach isn't necessarily a fabrication; it's a recognized legal theory that allows the Constitution to adapt to modern societal realities. To claim one side is *only* using gymnastics ignores the complexity of how legal meaning evolves over centuries. Both schools of thought represent legitimate, albeit opposing, approaches to constitutional interpretation.",
